      7          /***************************************************************************//**
      8           * Check if the MCU can sleep at that time. This function is called when the system
      9           * is about to go sleeping, with the interrupts disabled. It allows the software to
     10           * cancel going to sleep in case of a last-minute event occurred (window between the
     11           * function call and interrupt disable).
     12           *
     13           * @return  True, if the system can go to sleep.
     14           *          False, otherwise.
     15           *
     16           * @note  This function is called with the interrupt disabled and it MUST NOT be
     17           *        re-enabled.
     18           ******************************************************************************/
